  "final_answer": "Heena is a traditional ingredient that has been linked to the treatment of leg pain, with key compounds including copper, glucose, and ethanol. The compounds in Heena have been mapped to various drug equivalents, including:\n- Copper, which is identically mapped to Copper in Kogenate FS and has a likely mapping to Copper sulfate pentahydrate in several drugs.\n- Glucose, which is identically mapped to Glucose in Iveegam EN.\n- Ethanol, which has various mappings, including a likely mapping to Ethanol in several drugs, and a weak mapping to Alcohol ethanol in others.\n\nAccording to a Hadith, Hazrat Salma Umme Rafe’ said that Rasoolullah advised cupping for headache and Heena for leg pain, as mentioned in Abu Dawud: 3858. It is essential to consult a healthcare professional before using any traditional ingredients or drugs to ensure safe and effective treatment. Please consult a healthcare professional for personalized advice on using Heena for leg pain, as they can provide guidance on potential interactions and appropriate usage.",
